The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Saturday, May 29, 2004 				 Jute mills
																								Calcutta, May 28: Labour commissioner would hold tripartite meetings with labour unions and management of jute mills to discuss the impasse over closed units across the state, said labour minister Mohammed Amin, says a staff reporter.																								Already, 12 of the 54 jute mills in the state have closed down and at least 40,000 workers rendered jobless statewide.																								Labour secretary Ashok Mohan Chakraborty said Amin had a meeting today with the unions and managements that focused several jute mills that have shut their doors in quick succession. 
